<p>Another way of phrasing the symmetric difference of sets \(A\) and \(B\) is to say \(A \bigtriangleup B\) is the union of elements that are unique to each of \(A\) and \(B.\)  The shaded area in the Venn diagram below represents the symmetric difference of \(A\) and \(B\):</p>

<p><label for="set-symm-diff2" class="margin-toggle">âŠ•</label>
